cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR

The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a subfield of computer vision. The use of covariance matrices and Riemannian manifolds suggests that the paper may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of discriminative mapping and similarity vectors suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of Bregman matrix divergence suggests that the paper may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
